# Onec Query Strategy Reference

## Cheapest-first lookup table

- Platform syntax/API question:
  - `platform`
- Configuration object, requisite, type, tabular section, form field, form command:
  - `metadata`
- Why object/flag/button influences behavior:
  - `metadata -> code`
- Exact source text or raw XML confirmation:
  - `full`

## Good escalation examples

- `HTTP–°–Њ–µ–і–Є–љ–µ–љ–Є–µ.–Я–Њ–ї—Г—З–Є—В—М`
  - start with `platform`
- `Document.–†–µ–∞–ї–Є–Ј–∞—Ж–Є—П–Ґ–Њ–≤–∞—А–Њ–≤–£—Б–ї—Г–≥.–Ґ–Њ–≤–∞—А—Л.–Э–Њ–Љ–µ–љ–Ї–ї–∞—В—Г—А–∞`
  - start with `metadata`
- `–Ъ–∞–Ї —Д–ї–∞–≥ –£–Я–Ф –≤–ї–Є—П–µ—В –љ–∞ –Ј–∞–њ–Є—Б—М –і–Њ–Ї—Г–Љ–µ–љ—В–∞`
  - `metadata` to identify the flag and forms
  - `code` to find readers, writers, and handlers
  - `full` only if the code index is insufficient

## Anti-patterns

- Do not build `code.pack` for every task by default.
- Do not use `full` as the first lookup layer.
- Do not answer platform questions from configuration packs if `platform` can answer them.
- Do not mix results from multiple targets without naming the target.
